	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=283834><span id=Scholar>The One and Only Maatogaeoth</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>23 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.85]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The biggest issue I see is that with the augs you're talking about is the huge number of adventures you'd have to go on to get them.&nbsp;&nbsp;You're list showed 867 points just from North Ro!  At the &quot;recommended&quot; level for this robe (45) that would take a huge amount of time.  I have both a 65 enchanter and a 51 ranger that are doing dungeons and at 51, the ranger is only getting around 13 points per normal adventure.  Hard adventures only double that.  So you're looking at cranking out 67 North Ro adventures just to get the augs you list?  By the time you go through that many, this robe is going to be low on the scale of things that you would want.<br><br>This robe is similar to the breastplate in Butcherblock.  Decent stats for the level recommended and only 150 points.  So with some decent work and a good run, you could easily get these in a week or even less.  Now, for the time spent on that, these 150 point items are very nice.  Those augments that are 300/500/and even more points are more geared to the upper 50's and low 60's crowd, where they can save up some points and get a really nice upgrade to what they have.<br><br>I agree that the robe described is a great robe, but I think the time required to get them isn't worth that combination.  From what I've seen, it's always best to save up your points for the big items.  Less frustrating than spending points on items that you're just going to upgrade later on.  The biggest annoyance I've come across is with the nice augments that go into gear that gets replaced.<br><br>Also, there is a lot of nice drops in the actual adventure.  My ranger just got a bow from a North Ro adventure that was a very nice upgrade.  Speed 28, base 20 damage with a +8 damage modifier along with dex +15, wis +10 and a 120 point Flame Arrow proc.  I've yet to get it to proc, but I've only used it about 60 shots since I got it.  It's new, what can I say.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
